    <h1 style="font-size:28px;"> Properties and Values</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 21px;">The values are the things that the properties have in CSS. These properties show text color, background-color, font-size, font-weight and etc.<br> These properties differentiate the content of the html from each other. For example, if you want the heading of the content of your project to be white color, then you would use inline css.<br> In this method you would write style="color:green" inside the h1 or h2 or h3 or h4 or h5 or h6 tags</p>
